<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Charm1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Charm,</orth> subst., 1) magic power, means of a magic influence: <cit><quote>honest fear, bewitched with lust's foul c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 173" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 173</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who, with a c. joined to their suffered labour, I have left asleep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 231</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 231</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.95.88" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl> Tp. Epil. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.215" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.5.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 5, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.13" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 8, 13</bibl> etc. -- <emph>Charm</emph> and <emph>spell</emph> placed together as two different things: <cit><quote>she works by --s, by spells, by the figure,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.185" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 185</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>never harm, nor spell nor c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>unchain your spirits now with spelling --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 31</bibl></cit> (<cit><quote>charming spells,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 2</bibl></cit>). <cit><quote>your vessels and your spells provide, your --s and every thing beside,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.5.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 5, 19</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>spell</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>